  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In the construction phase, the focus is on monitoring the broader organization's architecture, infrastructure and&#xD;
    interfaces to external systems for changes that may affect the solution.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The important area of work in this sphere is:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;b>Update the architectural context:&lt;/b> The purpose is to update the details about the architectural constraints,&#xD;
        boundaries and interfaces posed by external systems and existing infrastructure with which the solution interfaces.&#xD;
        This information is captured in the to-be &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Models&lt;/a> and to-be &lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_architecture_document_A73E67D4.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{D3A0CA96-30AD-4461-9386-A3EC9A7E879F}&quot;>Business Architecture Documents&lt;/a>. &#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            Updating the architectural context is done by performing the following RUP task (note that other RUP tasks and&#xD;
            artifacts of the business modeling and analysis &amp;amp; design disciplines may be applicable, but this is the&#xD;
            minimum recommended set):&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
